{"questionId":"13597","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n</math></span> be a random variable which follows a normal distribution with mean <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\mu \">\n  <mi>μ</mi>\n</math></span>. Given that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {X < \\mu&nbsp; - 5} \\right) = 0.2\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo>&lt;</mo>\n      <mi>μ</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.2</mn>\n</math></span> , find</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {X < \\mu&nbsp; + 5\\,\\left| {\\,X > \\mu&nbsp; - 5} \\right.} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo>&lt;</mo>\n      <mi>μ</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>|</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>&gt;</mo>\n          <mi>μ</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo fence=\"true\" stretchy=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\"></mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {X < \\mu&nbsp; + 5\\,\\left| {\\,X > \\mu&nbsp; - 5} \\right.} \\right) = \\frac{{{\\text{P}}\\left( {X > \\mu&nbsp; - 5 \\cap X < \\mu&nbsp; + 5} \\right)}}{{{\\text{P}}\\left( {X > \\mu&nbsp; - 5} \\right)}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo>&lt;</mo>\n      <mi>μ</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>|</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>&gt;</mo>\n          <mi>μ</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo fence=\"true\" stretchy=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\"></mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>P</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>&gt;</mo>\n          <mi>μ</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n          <mo>∩</mo>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>&lt;</mo>\n          <mi>μ</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>P</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>&gt;</mo>\n          <mi>μ</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{{{\\text{P}}\\left( {\\mu&nbsp; - 5 < X < \\mu&nbsp; + 5} \\right)}}{{{\\text{P}}\\left( {X > \\mu&nbsp; - 5} \\right)}}\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>P</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>μ</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n          <mo>&lt;</mo>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>&lt;</mo>\n          <mi>μ</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>P</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>&gt;</mo>\n          <mi>μ</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{{0.6}}{{0.8}}\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.8</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for denominator is independent of the previous <em><strong>A</strong></em> marks.</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>use of diagram&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Only award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> if the region&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\mu&nbsp; - 5 < X < \\mu&nbsp; + 5\">\n  <mi>μ</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>X</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>μ</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n</math></span> is indicated and used.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {X > \\mu&nbsp; - 5} \\right) = 0.8\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo>&gt;</mo>\n      <mi>μ</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.8</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {\\mu&nbsp; - 5 < X < \\mu&nbsp; + 5} \\right) = 0.6\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>μ</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <mo>&lt;</mo>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo>&lt;</mo>\n      <mi>μ</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.6</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Probabilities can be shown on the diagram.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{{0.6}}{{0.8}}\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.8</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{3}{4}\\,\\,\\, = \\left( {0.75} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.75</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13597","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ1.H_6b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"P ( X < μ + 5 | X > μ − 5 ) .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.12—Z values, inverse normal to find mean and standard deviation"],"memberSect